grove-registry — third-party query file attribution
===================================================

This registry redistributes tree-sitter query files (`tags.scm`, `locals.scm`)
sourced from upstream projects. Their grammars (`grammar.wasm`) are built from the
tree-sitter grammar repositories listed per language in each `manifest.json`
(`source.repo` / `source.rev`).

locals.scm
----------

Scope-aware go-to-def queries. Sources and their licenses:

- ruby, scala, julia, javascript
  From the official tree-sitter grammar repositories (see each language's
  `manifest.json` `source`). Licensed MIT.

- python, go, java, c_sharp, c, cpp, rust
  From nvim-treesitter (https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter),
  licensed Apache-2.0. Each file retains a provenance header pointing at its
  upstream path. The `cpp` file is **modified by grove**: a single
  `(init_declarator ...)` pattern was appended to capture plainly-initialized
  local variables (e.g. `int y = x;`), which the upstream file omits.

  Apache License 2.0: http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0
  A copy of the Apache-2.0 license text is available at the URL above and in the
  nvim-treesitter repository's LICENSE file.

tags.scm
--------

Definition/reference queries, from the official tree-sitter grammar repositories
(per-language `manifest.json` `source`), with grove-curated additions where noted
in `registry-sources.json` (`extra_tags`). Licensed under each grammar repo's
license (predominantly MIT).
